Define a Type called User:
    It has a public Name (Text).
    It has a private Status Note (Text, default is "new").

    When created using name:
        Set its Name to name.

    When updated:
        Set its Status Note to "changed".

    It can "Rename" as public using new name:
        Set its Name to new name.
        Print its Name.

Define a Type called Admin which is a kind of User:
    It can "Rename" as public using new name:
        Ask super to "Rename" using new name.
        Print "Renamed by admin.".

Create an Admin called admin user using "Alice".
Print admin user.
Ask admin user to "Rename" using "Bob".
Print admin user.
